Chinese President Xi Jinping on SaturdayÂ sent a congratulatory message to Bola Tinubu on his election as Nigerian president. Nigeria is China's important strategic partner in Africa, Xi pointed out in his message. The relationship between the two countries has maintained a good momentum of development over the years, Xi said, adding that practical cooperation in various fields has yielded fruitful results. The two countries support each other on issues concerning each other's core interests and major concerns and cooperate closely in international and regional affairs, Xi said. The Chinese president said he attaches great importance to the development of China-Nigeria relations, expressing willingness to work with Tinubu to promote the China-Nigeria strategic partnership to a new level. (Cover: Bola Tinubu meets with supporters at the Party's campaign headquarters after winning the presidential elections in Abuja, Nigeria, March 1, 2023. /CFP)